B-_iId2v_16KsflnFSlFSKOsxeGkzsf65-E5UaD4Z4vSaDXsTJHY8oBTR0VmdTtKZ2_VzFA6dyZSp5uPX1KnFZ6wAA1DALYA2AzaOitwUB2k_5PJOV6vcHLVXYjf5rnubq4qBLdimXvb-WyfzA9LrWQVUUpYKsuiNy677nN2kn5xiX2GJW5GzsphAdXi5vufBynE3V5S3YtkiDYnXFBpbg46VfOdOaQ-hum0uliaAGWKZ7G7gMqbAhgcsUgyhfHGzrlpfag4MLSVOMcc9_GbkuWE0yMRLkNBSTZXg3VpaccHi1ffLQEio_KEZPIht7XqDnZe9lmgUBng-uMYGsZP-1JevPEBQUwHKz2Yn4nEW1Jh4f1bwXplrqORrKHkLHoVOJu_QCLoKjaNkIZJZzFGRkI_ZDnTXuiugMKTTqz9k7Kkmcrl-NoTElskdqWXvs6XOZ_OPmqYS781uN-sT0qzrCqK1kXRZIk9ENDo0r7NseDWF9W3K7bLAi4UtJNE2Wt8k-hTne3pkljnLHZnd-rJJ-DrOJ9SVZJc8NinZWymNYpZ3r6PmHHm06oB8NIAY7pELHscWwp8Vo5RZ2KXt9UJQKdwkL-wYjMa1m5QQRvrk5EOq6aXGPBhedvjJz3UDJ7WWVscGgwSTNTLXQPUZxKFlH9CIU0HLc2qkyREsBaBmpJ0tLCLcTfnopYhPtUVroyxTZXhrQjLGnCKXviZFesiE4AiXgxcP-POxVgRlKnCtZyIiS7RcKLEBBPDZjUTSOyeAxuIQYiKnZyj--mq29bUqdkJnI2qx9BjW4K6ExlSyYQtCl-0cLvZNaZbnYYxsnr7xvtqUIIhTDcZPvnwosJnUoqTIebMymlGOTEGPh6OUd2bMNfv9f_7ys9UIZMBWzmOyIGClUDnDiRK4R7xx1rDRnIFxFFkUyX2TIGvZ0hRzi3hK_F3aGvGBHrO8WVBUL8LrllfpcP-VO_TAYJ76X7plQ_qX7cSPWjLgy8gxIE2GEJ9W7xszEK59zR2QdY421p_CU46Jv_V4UtrNjYw9TuVdNNHjUUKA77_pHc8S1y33l2neacl3wFrs_gRxhKK71Sj_WOsNqnrHb_JIS5mCacq0gUVCOA7jNO3QDAg8zWTKE_cRMau1zvPHccu3wJmefPhyYKvF8mg8JG1Usx\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the dynamic class loading pattern. It can be really useful, but it feels like it might be too broad to implement effectively and isn’t natively supported in some cases. I wonder how to refine it or if there are specific scenarios where it truly shines. It's interesting to evaluate its strengths and weaknesses, especially when considering how it interacts with different programming environments. Let’s take a closer look at practical applications!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating error handling in tests**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the Native test has metadata from the agent, which is good. I need to decide if I should catch errors, but the rule suggests not catching unsupported errors during ordinary reflection. So, I should avoid wrapping error handling around field resets. Currently, the approach seems to catch errors around everything, including reflection setup. In the test, I’ll only catch errors related to dynamic class loading, ensuring I don’t incorrectly swallow unsupported errors. Could we reset fields before the try?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jnfQ6ybf4AIrtEOtMcBRXL21|fc_084e99528762e5290169f64d0db99881958950179dbb6fa923", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/src/test/java/legacy/junit3/LoadingTestCollectorTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import junit.runner.LoadingTestCollector;\nimport junit.runner.TestCollector;\n", "newText": "import junit.runner.LoadingTestCollector;\n"}, {"oldText": "import java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\n"}, {"oldText": "        String previousClassPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.class.path\", classpathRoot.toString());\n", "newText": "        clearLegacyClassLiteralCaches();\n        String previousClassPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.class.path\", classpathRoot.toString());\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void freshlyLoadedCollectorInitializesLegacyClassLiteralsDuringCollection() throws Exception {\n        copyClassFile(PublicJunit3Case.class, classpathRoot);\n        String previousClassPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.class.path\", classpathRoot.toString());\n        try {\n            TestCollector collector = newFreshLoadingTestCollector();\n            List<String> collectedTestNames = collectTestNames(collector.collectTests());\n\n            assertThat(collectedTestNames).contains(PublicJunit3Case.class.getName());\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\n        } finally {\n            restoreProperty(\"java.class.path\", previousClassPath);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static TestCollector newFreshLoadingTestCollector() throws ReflectiveOperationException {\n        ClassLoader parent = LoadingTestCollectorTest.class.getClassLoader();\n        ClassLoader classLoader = new FreshLoadingTestCollectorClassLoader(parent);\n        return classLoader.loadClass(LoadingTestCollector.class.getName())\n                .asSubclass(TestCollector.class)\n                .getConstructor()\n                .newInstance();\n    }\n\n", "newText": ""}, {"oldText": "    private static void rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(Error error) {\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class FreshLoadingTestCollectorClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private static final String TARGET_CLASS_NAME = \"junit.runner.LoadingTestCollector\";\n\n        FreshLoadingTestCollectorClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!TARGET_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = defineTargetClass();\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n\n        private Class<?> defineTargetClass() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            String resourceName = TARGET_CLASS_NAME.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n            try (InputStream inputStream = getParent().getRes