 ordinary reflection. So, I should avoid wrapping error handling around field resets. Currently, the approach seems to catch errors around everything, including reflection setup. In the test, I’ll only catch errors related to dynamic class loading, ensuring I don’t incorrectly swallow unsupported errors. Could we reset fields before the try?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jnfQ6ybf4AIrtEOtMcBRXL21|fc_084e99528762e5290169f64d0db99881958950179dbb6fa923", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/src/test/java/legacy/junit3/LoadingTestCollectorTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import junit.runner.LoadingTestCollector;\nimport junit.runner.TestCollector;\n", "newText": "import junit.runner.LoadingTestCollector;\n"}, {"oldText": "import java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\n"}, {"oldText": "        String previousClassPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.class.path\", classpathRoot.toString());\n", "newText": "        clearLegacyClassLiteralCaches();\n        String previousClassPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.class.path\", classpathRoot.toString());\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void freshlyLoadedCollectorInitializesLegacyClassLiteralsDuringCollection() throws Exception {\n        copyClassFile(PublicJunit3Case.class, classpathRoot);\n        String previousClassPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.class.path\", classpathRoot.toString());\n        try {\n            TestCollector collector = newFreshLoadingTestCollector();\n            List<String> collectedTestNames = collectTestNames(collector.collectTests());\n\n            assertThat(collectedTestNames).contains(PublicJunit3Case.class.getName());\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\n        } finally {\n            restoreProperty(\"java.class.path\", previousClassPath);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static TestCollector newFreshLoadingTestCollector() throws ReflectiveOperationException {\n        ClassLoader parent = LoadingTestCollectorTest.class.getClassLoader();\n        ClassLoader classLoader = new FreshLoadingTestCollectorClassLoader(parent);\n        return classLoader.loadClass(LoadingTestCollector.class.getName())\n                .asSubclass(TestCollector.class)\n                .getConstructor()\n                .newInstance();\n    }\n\n", "newText": ""}, {"oldText": "    private static void rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(Error error) {\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class FreshLoadingTestCollectorClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private static final String TARGET_CLASS_NAME = \"junit.runner.LoadingTestCollector\";\n\n        FreshLoadingTestCollectorClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!TARGET_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = defineTargetClass();\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n\n        private Class<?> defineTargetClass() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            String resourceName = TARGET_CLASS_NAME.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n            try (InputStream inputStream = getParent().getResourceAsStream(resourceName)) {\n                if (inputStream == null) {\n                    throw new ClassNotFoundException(TARGET_CLASS_NAME);\n                }\n                byte[] classBytes = inputStream.readAllBytes();\n                return defineClass(TARGET_CLASS_NAME, classBytes, 0, classBytes.length);\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(TARGET_CLASS_NAME, exception);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n", "newText": "    private static void rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(Error error) {\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void clearLegacyClassLiteralCaches() throws ReflectiveOperationException {\n        clearLegacyClassLiteralCache(\"class$junit$framework$Test\");\n        clearLegacyClassLiteralCache(\"class$java$lang$String\");\n    }\n\n    private static void clearLegacyClassLiteralCache(String fieldName) throws ReflectiveOperationException {\n        Field field = LoadingTestCollector.class.getDeclaredField(fieldName);\n        field.setAccessible(true);\n        field.set(null, null);\n    }\n\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 898, "output": 2759, "cacheRead": 47616, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51273, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777749233735, "responseId": "resp_084e99528762e5290169f64cf251e88195b8752325163ac2bb"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_jnfQ6ybf4AIrtEOtMcBRXL21|fc_084e99528762e5290169f64d0db99881958950179dbb6fa923", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Found 2 occurrences of edits[2] in tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/src/test/java/legacy/junit3/LoadingTestCollectorTest.java. Each oldText must be unique. Please provide more context to make it unique."}], "details": {}, 